chunk_text: This document presents the findings from the annual compliance audit conducted for fiscal year 2024. The audit assessed the effectiveness of risk management controls across all business units.

The risk assessment framework identifies and evaluates potential compliance risks using a standardized methodology. Each risk is categorized by likelihood and impact to determine priority for mitigation efforts.

The control framework consists of preventive, detective, and corrective controls designed to mitigate identified risks. All controls are mapped to specific risks and regulatory requirements to ensure comprehensive coverage.

Critical finding: Access control review identified gaps in user provisioning and deprovisioning processes. Current manual workflows create delays averaging 5-7 business days, increasing risk exposure during transition periods.
OCR quality was lower than expected in scanned appendix pages. Some text segments required manual verification to ensure accuracy. This affected approximately 12% of total document content.

Implement automated user lifecycle management system to reduce provisioning delays and improve audit trail completeness. Estimated implementation timeline is 6-9 months with expected ROI within 18 months.

Overall risk posture has improved compared to prior year, with 87% of high-priority controls operating effectively. Remaining gaps are being addressed through corrective action plans with executive sponsorship.
